commit.message:
Don't change user's chosen priority of org target finder

This fixes #709.
Add tips for Vertico users to get which-key like behaviour

Strip text properties in embark-insert

This fixes a behavior change inadvertently introduced when
embark-insert became a multitarget action.
Allow scrolling embark action list in pixel-scroll-precision-mode

Fix potential bug in dired export

It seems like in some rare cases default-directory may not be set to
exactly the argument we passed to dired-noselect, but
default-directory always seems to point to the correct hierarchy root
for the current dired buffer.
Add key binding to comment out defun or s-expression

Fix bug in which after wgrep g no longer reruns the export

Correct fix this time.

Revert "Fix bug in which after wgrep g no longer reruns the export"

This reverts commit e1a8c0e9db26c6bf41c9c10adfd05e30fc87d599.

I forgot that this style of key binding introduces another bug: it
permanently modifies grep-mode-map giving g the wrong binding in
non-embark-export grep buffers.

commit.message: Fix bug in which after wgrep g no longer reruns the export
Document new grep exporter for consult-location

Refactor the two grep exporters

- Almost all shared code has been moved to a new function
  embark-consult--export-grep, which takes care of putting the buffer
  in grep mode and preparing the header and footer for wgrep.

- The result format for the new grep exporter for consult-location
  has been uniformized with the grep exporter for consult-grep and
  with the built-in grep and rgrep commands.

- A couple of bugs in the new grep exporter for consult-location have
  been fixed: the matches were not counted and the list of non-file
  buffers was not computed correctly.
Remove unused variable
Fix merge conflicts and address oantolin's feedback
Tiny wording fix in documentation
Minimal indicator is not on by default

Use org-element only in org-mode buffers (fixes #698)

The org-element parser will start raising errors in non-org-mode
buffers in future org releases. We were using it in org-agenda buffers
too, but the benefit is almost non-existent: by far the most
important org targets in agenda buffers are headings and links and
those target finders do not use org-element.
Use list-matching-lines-prefix-face for occur export

Better match text properties of real occur buffers

The rear-nonsticky property was letting users edit the headers, as
reported by @jdtsmith in #697.

Make parts of the occur export buffer read-only (fixes #697)

With this change we match which portions of the built-in occur's
output are read-only. Some external packages such as iedit rely on
those text properties.
Comment out eldoc configuration, since it is intrusive
Bump version number to 1.0 🎉
Merge branch 'consult-grep-dwim'
Document new consult async dwim behavior
Allow multitarget actions to use around hooks
